- You can use modules to make your terraform more organized

- use third party modules
   - Modules from github
     module "module_example" {
        source = "github.com/*"
     }

- Reuse parts of your code
   - to setup network in AWS - VPC

- You can also use a module from a local folder 
  module "m-example" {
    source = "./module-example"
  }

- You can pass arguments to a module

- Inside the module folder, you just have tf files
  - vars.tf
  - clusters.tf
  - output.tf
